commit_message:
Add warning for 2 compute periodic checks

2bfc7171c23d0595aa7f8680271778bc58cb28ba
Add warning to periodic_task with interval 0
added some check for deprecating in Icehouse and
in Juno 324d951667aa973955cebd6e49d98af6f2aba916
removed those warning and make the change.

_heal_instance_info_cache and _poll_volume_usage
are missing during previous patch, so this patch
adds it.

oslo already checked _periodic_spacing if
it's < 0, then the periodic task is disabled
it's = 0, then the periodic task spacing is default (60)
so no need to check it in nova manager.

Those check will be warned at Kilo and removed at L release.

Change-Id: I12d55b600dc1fda38cc7b7405f57d8dd91ee3d38

commit_message:
Change request for discussion on default template implementation

This simple CR has been created for feedback on implementation
details for default templates. It is not meant to merge.
Please add thoughts to comments. There will be a thread
on [openstack-dev][sahara] as well. Once we have some
kind of consensus we can modify the existing spec and
add more detail.

Two primary questions at this point, see comments for
more detail.

* Should this separate CLI for default-templates tie in
to Sahara at the conductor level, or the db api level?

* Do we want/need the CLI to authenticate to keystone,
or do we just create necessary elements of a context
manually?

Change-Id: I1bb18ab74616f1f1ec78e6b1c791d2a302dd0e0d
Partial-implements: blueprint default-templates

commit_message:
Second set of negative functional tests for secrets

This set of tests addresses a bug that causes a failure when
retrieving a secret that is not valid. If you provide a url with
an incorrectly formated UUID a proper message is displayed.
If you provide a correctly formated uuid that is not a valid secret
or the secret is expired it returns a secret object with errors
for each object saying attribute is not defined.

Change-Id: I45fa72f7ec37b3469f80c5593eba8335ae5db6e7

commit_message:
Add support for Neutron agents local state reports

It makes sense to detect additional Neutron agents problems like inability to
communicate with neutron server over message queue.
So in order to provide additional hints to monitoring scripts 'local reports'
are introduced. A local report is a piece of information written to a file
by neutron agent about status of certain kind of operations.
This patch adds support for them to Pacemaker OCF scripts.

This feature is experimental and is disabled by default.

Change-Id: Ie35ec805ce96e7a27fc699c9114c719d8cdcddef
Implements: blueprint neutron-agents-local-reports

commit_message:
Fedora 21 tftp files fix (copy in syslinux modules)

For newer version of syslinux we also need to copy in any
ldlinux modules as well. This resolves PXE boot issues
when using a seed/undercloud build with new distributions
like Fedora 21.

Change-Id: Ide269386372dd4fae38174bb06b7a1b84a3aa0c5
Closes-bug: #1429499

commit_message:
Update tests for optional sslv3

According to the linked bug, Debian has removed sslv3 from their
Python packages completely, so we need to make it optional like
sslv2 was.

The functional code changes were made in
I41c6598cb874b79c391f8b4e4607b85c4660bd2f but the tests weren't
updated in that change, so this will still have issues once
development environments update to newer Python versions.

Change-Id: Id69701978d7a1701885bf17507a1f369e1035747
Closes-Bug: 1395095

[{'number': 7, 'created': '2015-01-05 21:04:00.000000000', 'files': ['keystoneclient/common/cms.py'], 'message': "token signing support alternative message digest

The functions for creating signed tokens in common.cms always used
sha256 for the message digest. This might be inadequate in the future
so the digest algorithm shouldn't be hard-coded. A parameter is added

commit_message:
token signing support alternative message digest

The functions for creating signed tokens in common.cms always used
sha256 for the message digest. This might be inadequate in the future
so the digest algorithm shouldn't be hard-coded. A parameter is added
to allow choosing a different digest algorithm.

SecurityImpact

Change-Id: Ie19d093d0494443ce4cd880ae1f92dffd5c361ef
Related-Bug: #1362343

commit_message:
Remove use of DEVSTACK_GATE_TESTR_ARTIFACT_TARGET

The intention was to have this variable allow functional jobs to reuse
the code used to archive testr artifacts for tempest, but the
requirement to have testr installed system-wide (or specify a target
venv where it is installed) let to pursuing use of project-config's
run-tox.sh script instead.

Change-Id: Ib932423bbeec76ae49b93e28e9fc693d7ee57bed

subject: Fix for unwanted plus sign in sublists
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-03-09 01:10:41.000000000', 'files': ['doc/source/index.rst', 'openstackdocstheme/theme/openstackdocs/static/js/docs.js', 'doc/source/BBtest.rst'], 'message': 'Fix for unwanted plus sign in sublists

A plus sign with gray background appears next to a bulleted list inside
a numbered list. It does NOT appear in all other sublist cases such as
bullet list nested inside numbered list.

The plus sign is caused by CSS class "docs-has-sub", defined in
combined.css.

Example - given this RST

    #. Number 1
    #. Number 2

       * Bullet 1

the following HTML (or similar) is rendered:

    <ol>
    <li> Number 1
    <li class="docs-has-sub">Number 2
       <ul>
       <li>Bullet 1
    ....

Where does the "docs-has-sub" come from? It has been added to the <li>
element by the following line in docs.js:

    $('ol > li:has(ul)').addClass('docs-has-sub');

The purpose of this line seems to be implementation of an expandable and
collapsable sublist. The plus sign indicates to the user that the list
can be expanded. Perhaps this implementation is incomplete?

Since the Javascript line affects all bulleted sublists of numbered
lists, not only expandable ones, I am removing it. The expansion feature
has to be implemented differently.

Closes-Bug: #1417291
Change-Id: Ib6ecd176ca0e1c788a9277ebbf38ea91b6b891ce
'}]
commit_message:
Fix for unwanted plus sign in sublists

A plus sign with gray background appears next to a bulleted list inside
a numbered list. It does NOT appear in all other sublist cases such as
bullet list nested inside numbered list.

The plus sign is caused by CSS class "docs-has-sub", defined in
combined.css.

Example - given this RST

    #. Number 1
    #. Number 2

       * Bullet 1

the following HTML (or similar) is rendered:

    <ol>
    <li> Number 1
    <li class="docs-has-sub">Number 2
       <ul>
       <li>Bullet 1
    ....

Where does the "docs-has-sub" come from? It has been added to the <li>
element by the following line in docs.js:

    $('ol > li:has(ul)').addClass('docs-has-sub');

The purpose of this line seems to be implementation of an expandable and
collapsable sublist. The plus sign indicates to the user that the list
can be expanded. Perhaps this implementation is incomplete?

Since the Javascript line affects all bulleted sublists of numbered
lists, not only expandable ones, I am removing it. The expansion feature
has to be implemented differently.

Closes-Bug: #1417291
Change-Id: Ib6ecd176ca0e1c788a9277ebbf38ea91b6b891ce

[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-11-26 15:54:41.000000000', 'files': ['nova/virt/vmwareapi/driver.py'], 'message': 'VMware: fix exception when multiple compute nodes are running

A number of operations in the VMwareVCDriver class first validate
that instances node is the cluster that is mapped to the compute
node. This is problematic when the compute nodes have different
configurations, for example, each compute node is mapped to a
different cluster.

In this case many operations that are just performing instance operations
will fail. This patch ensure that all instance operations that do not
require a cluster or volume will make use of the base _vmops class.
This is due to the fact that it only requires the instance details
to interface with the VC and there are no specific cluster operations.

Change-Id: I2bc38a480f2feb12ea41e7d28f80b29dd49a79b8
Closes-bug: #1345460
(cherry picked from commit 8e4a9156f4dccf003970848c28b8a9d15c55212d)
'}]
commit_message:
VMware: fix exception when multiple compute nodes are running

A number of operations in the VMwareVCDriver class first validate
that instances node is the cluster that is mapped to the compute
node. This is problematic when the compute nodes have different
configurations, for example, each compute node is mapped to a
different cluster.

In this case many operations that are just performing instance operations
will fail. This patch ensure that all instance operations that do not
require a cluster or volume will make use of the base _vmops class.
This is due to the fact that it only requires the instance details
to interface with the VC and there are no specific cluster operations.

Change-Id: I2bc38a480f2feb12ea41e7d28f80b29dd49a79b8
Closes-bug: #1345460
(cherry picked from commit 8e4a9156f4dccf003970848c28b8a9d15c55212d)

commit_message:
Update Datera's export to avoid deprecated keys

The export call has been updated in Datera. The old location for the IQN
has moved. This updates the Kilo driver with support of looking in the
new location. The Juno driver will remain using the old location.

Closes-Bug: #1430024
Change-Id: I28a76ef849c2d3a0e4d08c5d0707e28d9617f534

commit_message:
IBP: Package for image building script

Created rpm package for a set of scripts
which are for building target OS images.
We need this package in order to be able
to install these scripts on the master node.

Implements: blueprint ibp-build-ubuntu-images

commit_message:
Build ubuntu on master node

In order to build targer images on master node astute will call that
script inside of mcollective docker container.

Script accepts one positional parameter as json encoded data string.

Later, it will be reworked into better python tool for building
images.

Implements blueprint ibp-build-ubuntu-images

Change-Id: I5a1761167bceb9a2670a467f4b856f7019784a62

commit_message:
Do not filter empty strings

Empty strings shouldn't be filtered from requests, as we have
explicitly set some attributes to be optional and actually
differentiate between null and empty attributes in the server side. So
now, only attributes containing None are filtered and empty strings
are actually passed to the server.

Change-Id: Ia048d7de6bcbc12317930eeccc009b6b0db10e13
Closes-bug: #1420445

commit_message:
Adds basic ironicclient functional testing

This moves unit tests to ironicclient/tests/unit and adds a new test
directory at ironicclient/tests/functional.  These are meant to be
functional tests that are run against a living cloud (presumably deployed
by devstack as part of a gating job).  They depend on a test.conf to exist
that contains admin user credentials for said cloud.  This includes a simple
run_functional.sh script that is meant to create that and serve as the entry
point for running the tests from a devstack post_test_hook.

Change-Id: I11570c3e22e4f80b94d0643dca6ed8231217c877

commit_message:
Do not provision more than 50 nodes at time

Now, similar to deploy part it can be set
how many nodes may be provisioned at the
same time. By default it is 50 nodes.
It is useful for bigger environments where
provisioning 100 or 200 nodes at the same time
may lead to random bugs.

blueprint: 200-nodes-support
DocImpact

Change-Id: I275ec41ec9b0e239c3ef77ae379e81cab0a92804

commit_message:
Use update_attrs to handle updating servers

After we put update_attrs in, we got the ability to make updating pretty
easy. This currently offers the same thing as passing an already updated
Resource object into Connection.update, but I think there's value here
in how it's used to bring consistency.

[{'number': 3, 'created': '2015-02-27 03:57:15.000000000', 'files': ['tox.ini'], 'message': 'Update default tox envlist to match voting gate checks

Remove not-yet supported py3* environments.

Note the removed environments (py33,py34) are still supported via
explicit `tox -e`, it's only the default set that is changed here.

ObPoliticalDisclaimer:

This in no way diminishes the importance of py3 support.  In fact, the
intention is quite the opposite:

One day py3x will be supported and the py3x test will be expected to
pass.  Meanwhile, if everyone has been trained to run selective `tox
-epy27` tests then they will be unaware of the py3x status change and
won't be testing their code against py3 - or alternatively they will
believe that py3x failures are "normal" and to be ignored.

The hope with doing this change now is that we will (re)train people
that the default list of tox tests are expected to pass, and any
failures need to be investigated.

Change-Id: I992e1d6b35aa7c516c9ce14e606bbe32e895a4f0
'}]
commit_message:
Update default tox envlist to match voting gate checks

Remove not-yet supported py3* environments.

Note the removed environments (py33,py34) are still supported via
explicit `tox -e`, it's only the default set that is changed here.

ObPoliticalDisclaimer:

This in no way diminishes the importance of py3 support.  In fact, the
intention is quite the opposite:

One day py3x will be supported and the py3x test will be expected to
pass.  Meanwhile, if everyone has been trained to run selective `tox
-epy27` tests then they will be unaware of the py3x status change and
won't be testing their code against py3 - or alternatively they will
believe that py3x failures are "normal" and to be ignored.

The hope with doing this change now is that we will (re)train people
that the default list of tox tests are expected to pass, and any
failures need to be investigated.

Change-Id: I992e1d6b35aa7c516c9ce14e606bbe32e895a4f0

commit_message:
Transform IPAddress to string when creating port

If ip address is provided when running nova boot, nova compute
will invoke neutron client to create a port. However, the ip
address parameter is an IPAddress object so neutron client will
fail to send the request to neutron server. Transform IPAddress
object to string to address this issue.

Conflicts:
	nova/tests/unit/network/test_neutronv2.py

Change-Id: I858cca475748795aa2532f32bfe0f1443b30966f
Closes-Bug: #1408529
(cherry picked from commit aae858a246e20b1bf55004517b5d9ab28968190a)

commit_message:
Use tls_checks in HAProxy config

Allow configuration of whether TLS checks are enabled in HAProxy. This
change works in conjunction with
I6a96ccaa252be97bfa256c406a99de69bbc647f6 to specify whether the health
checks are run with TLS. If the deployer wants to run a TLS enabled
cloud they can set this option to make sure HAProxy uses the correct
health checks.

Change-Id: I5fa8deae921c61f5976d6594ad204a45309857a6

commit_message:
Add key/cert to secure MySQL clustering with TLS

Accept MysqlClusterSSLCertificate and MysqlClusterSSLCertificateKey
parameters and pass them through to the `mysql.cluster_certificate` and
`mysql.cluster_key` values. This parameter will be supplied at deploy
time and is typically a very long lived certificate as supplying a new
certificate would require the cluster to be restarted.

Change-Id: I92f612f792d13ca129e53edfa5213eb50f6d013a

subject: Add option for MySQL to bind locally
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-11-19 16:42:21.000000000', 'files': ['overcloud-source.yaml'], 'message': 'Add option for MySQL to bind locally

For services to talk to MySQL with TLS they must talk through stunnel in
client mode on the localhost. All connections from the database must go
through the stunnel at the client side and then through stunnel again at
server side. To facilitate this MySQL must be able to bind to localhost
to receive connections from stunnel and the services must be able
pointed at their localhost for MySQL connections out from stunnel.

The address for the database cannot be passed in as the control VIP is
not determined until deploy time.

Change-Id: I1c38386a83c7f27e6260143f0a5c0a4774fd7941
'}]
commit_message:
Add option for MySQL to bind locally

For services to talk to MySQL with TLS they must talk through stunnel in
client mode on the localhost. All connections from the database must go
through the stunnel at the client side and then through stunnel again at
server side. To facilitate this MySQL must be able to bind to localhost
to receive connections from stunnel and the services must be able
pointed at their localhost for MySQL connections out from stunnel.

The address for the database cannot be passed in as the control VIP is
not determined until deploy time.

Change-Id: I1c38386a83c7f27e6260143f0a5c0a4774fd7941

commit_message:
TLS checks field on HAProxy server cfg

Allow specification of whether the TLS checks should be used on this
server in HAProxy. To enable TLS checks the parameter 'tls_checks'
should be set along with the location of the ca-cert file with
'ca_cert_location' parameter.

Change-Id: I6a96ccaa252be97bfa256c406a99de69bbc647f6

commit_message:
Implement Scoped TSIG Key Support

Implement support for assiging a scope to a TSIG Key, allowing
certain TSIG keys to be assigned to either a Pool or a Zone.

TSIG Keys created via the V1 API, or are preexisting, are
assigned to the default pool.

Implements: blueprint mdns-designate-scoped-tsig
Change-Id: Ib9ae9727af0d447baf95e01ca81aef3ba494f49b

Added check for emptyness where in_ is being used

All the Neutron code was scanned for places where in_ is being used
and added checks to ensure that the input is not an empty sequence.

Python 2.7.9 doesn't support ssl.PROTOCOL_SSLv3 anymore due to the POODLE

commit_message:
Fixed ssl.PROTOCOL_SSLv3 not supported by Python 2.7.9

Python 2.7.9 doesn't support ssl.PROTOCOL_SSLv3 anymore due to the POODLE
attack. We should remove the use of ssl.PROTOCOL_SSLv3 in designate.

Change-Id: I3cfa4812fe11dafb40da2dc106780c4742796dff
Closes-Bug: 1430137

commit_message:
Stop using global cfg.CONF object

This replaces the cfg.CONF object by a conf object we create when we
prepare the service. This drops usage of ignominies such as import_opt()
or the config fixture.

It also fixes the clash we had with Ceilometer conf object that broke
the gate.

Change-Id: I4de8e274c0acd4707bdc52b783dc8ae0d3397d08

commit_message:
NEC plugin code split

- Removes main codes and unit tests of NEC plugin
- Add plugin-specific requirements.txt to the plugin dir.
- Move config to the plugin top dir
- Remove references of networking_nec from config module
  because it may prevent config guide generator.
- agent command can be moved to neutron/cmd/eventlet
  if some consensus has been made.

Closes-Bug: #1419396
Related to blueprint core-vendor-decomposition

Change-Id: I946e0f829e8f6251a63572331c783d7a7b5f6c01

commit_message:
Add concurrency support in new integration tests

Add support of parallel running tests.
Testr provide ability to setting number of processes for running tests.
By default concurrency = <num_of_cores_in_cpu>

partially implements bp: scenario-integration-tests

Change-Id: Iebe570382e463b485fbcb57608c3d6d82690e098

commit_message:
Collect errors in new integration tests

Decorator for collecting errors added.
If check failed then error will be saved and raised after running all
checks.
Here example of results:

+-----------------------------+--------+
| Check                       | Status |
+-----------------------------+--------+
| Create node group templates |   OK   |
| Create cluster template     |   OK   |
| Create cluster              |   OK   |
| Check EDP jobs              | FAILED |
| Cluster scaling             |   OK   |
| Check EDP jobs              | FAILED |
+-----------------------------+--------+

and example of traceback:

    Traceback (most recent call last):

      File "sahara/tests/scenario/base.py", line 56, in wrapper
        return fct(self, *args, **kwargs)

      File "sahara/tests/scenario/base.py", line 119, in check_run_jobs
        raise RuntimeError("OOPS")

    RuntimeError: OOPS

partially implements bp: scenario-integration-tests

Change-Id: Ied16b523c10eaa67e934b601419e76ad9b4b816a

commit_message:
Required fields' asterisk missing in 'Launch Instance' Dialog

In Launch Instance dialog, when the drop-down menu "Instance Boot
Source" is selected, it dynamically generates some more form
elements like- Image Name, Instance Snapshot, Volume Name, Volume
Snapshot, Volume, etc. If the form (i.e. Launch) is submitted
without these fields populated, it correctly rejects the submission
and highlights the missing fields, but the fields should be marked
with asterisk also so that they were clearly identified beforehand.

Change-Id: I3859e8474315bc3d5c0fc1ddf57932cf9957a592
Closes-Bug: #1277302

commit_message:
[EDP] Add Oozie Shell Job Type

This change adds the Shell job type, currently implemented for the
Oozie engine (per spec).

Oozie shell actions provide a great deal of flexibility and will
empower users to easily customize and extend the features of Sahara
EDP as needed. For example, a shell action could be used to manage
hdfs on the cluster, do pre or post processing for another job
launched from Sahara, or run a data processing job from a
specialized launcher that does extra configuration not otherwise
available from Sahara (ie, setting a special classpath for a Java job).

Change-Id: I0d8b59cf55cf583f0d24c2c8c2e487813d8ec716
Implements: blueprint add-edp-shell-action

commit_message:
Improve performance of _get_security_group_member_ips

Use set operations instead of using list.
Currently complexity of the method is O(n^2) where n is
amount of ips (amount of VMs in the network).
When amount of VM is big (large L2 domain), this method
can significantly load the controller.
Reduce method complexity to O(n) on average.

Change-Id: If1660e8227e5c5cd80d49ebcc6a2e06d33d31939
Closes-Bug: #1429753

commit_message:
Allow to specify multiple tests in run_tests.sh

Disable checking for unbound variables, as there is possibility that no
tests were specified. Example invocation:

run_tests.sh -n -t fuelclient/tests/test_client.py:TestAuthentication.test_wrong_credentials \
-t fuelclient/tests/test_client.py:TestDownloadUploadNodeAttributes

Additionally align shifts in getopt loop and remove
dead return from tox invocation.

DocImpact
Change-Id: I83a52b5f5467c9ea92dfafba9b92b700f7e76a38
Closes-Bug: 1420664

Add ability to get step id from context

commit_message:
IBP: Add python-urllib3 to fuel-agent rpm spec

In order to handle network errors correctly, python-urllib3 package
should be added to dependencies.

Fuel-agent relies on a recent version of python-requests (1.2.3),
which's known for raising exceptions from urllib3 library.

Partially implements: blueprint ibp-reconnect

Related-Bug: #1389120
Change-Id: I29495e03c3ad7c2697d554265b1b9c299187d875

commit_message:
Testing including content based on meta definitions

- To try it yourself, use:
sphinx-build -t admin_only \
doc/playground-user-guide/source/ \
doc/playground-user-guide/build/html/.
- Adds a simple scope.py extension, is this the right place for the extension
to be maintained, or should it go to openstack-doc-tools repo?
- This approach is a file-by-file approach for conditionals and will not do
conditional output based on a smaller chunk, such as a note or paragraph. Is
this a good approach for the RST migration? I have also investigated smaller
chunks with the .. only:: directive but it is wonky with non-para content such
as admonitions, tables, list items.

Change-Id: Ia9a44ea45319c97073ab4de55320c1851def232e

commit_message:
Support iSER driver within the ISCSITarget flow

This patch adds the support for the new iscsi_protocol parameter in KILO.
This parameter replaces the deprecated iSER driver.

The current supported values for iscsi_protocol are
'iscsi' or 'iser', with default to 'iscsi'.

Co-Authored-By: Gil Meir <gilmeir@mellanox.com>

Change-Id: I6e137c04115ab70427d24cd98839ad48ab345a32

subject: Pin python-openstackclient version to 0.4.1
revisions:
[{'number': 5, 'created': '2015-03-09 17:58:00.000000000', 'files': ['stack.sh'], 'message': 'Pin python-openstackclient version to 0.4.1

Currently, stable/icehouse devstack uses the latest version of
python-openstackclient which uses the new oslo form of imports
with underscores (e.g. import oslo_config). The new oslo
libraries that contain the new underscore imports are not used
in stable/icehouse so we need to pin python-openstackclient to
0.4.1.

Closes-Bug: #1427823
Change-Id: I363251c8d32a33e81a25c7279a202baf0eeb5cd3
'}]
commit_message:
Pin python-openstackclient version to 0.4.1

Currently, stable/icehouse devstack uses the latest version of
python-openstackclient which uses the new oslo form of imports
with underscores (e.g. import oslo_config). The new oslo
libraries that contain the new underscore imports are not used
in stable/icehouse so we need to pin python-openstackclient to
0.4.1.

Closes-Bug: #1427823
Change-Id: I363251c8d32a33e81a25c7279a202baf0eeb5cd3

commit_message:
alarming: add gnocchi alarm rules

Testing the API part of Gnocchi alarms within the Gnocchi tree is
a pain and doesn't really have senses.

So, this change moves the gnocchi alarms rules and evaluator that live
in Gnocchi tree to Ceilometer tree.

This also permits to add these new alarm rules into the documentation.

And add some tests that cannot be done on the gnocchi side.

DocImpact

Change-Id: I1bbc9f904d55b51cd1b3c51dcdfaf58f01bd9075

commit_message:
Fixed ssl.PROTOCOL_SSLv3 not supported by Python 2.7.9

Python 2.7.9 doesn't support ssl.PROTOCOL_SSLv3 by default anymore due to
security issues(POODLE attack). We should remove the usage of
ssl.PROTOCOL_SSLv3 in oslo-incubator.

Closes-Bug: 1395095

commit_message:
Compute: Catch binding failed exception while init host

While compute starts it will init all instances,
if an exception is raised from one instance
(e.g NovaException during plug_vifs), then the
compute process exits unexpectedly because of
this unhandled exception.
This commit changes the NovaException to more
appropriate VirtualInterfacePlugException and
catches it during init host, as well as the
instance is set to error state, with this change
the compute process can be started normally even
if this VirtualInterfacePlugException is raised.

Closes-bug: #1324041

Conflicts:
	nova/tests/unit/compute/test_compute_mgr.py
	nova/virt/ironic/driver.py
	nova/virt/libvirt/vif.py

Change-Id: Ia584dba66affb86787e3069df19bd17b89cb5c49
(cherry picked from commit 16ac50b1e760b7d20b840763b271a497b66ad5a5)

commit_message:
Remove setting use_floating_ips values

We remove the code to set use_floating_ips. In old code it was set
false if we do not use neutron. However, we cannot deploy clusters
with floating ips by that. So we just use the default value, which
is set True in Sahara.

Closes-Bug: #1426226
Change-Id: Idfcdc5ab776681ddc740dc12035e04da349ea089

commit_message:
Remove unviewable data from dashboard images (gif/png)

Images can have metadata that does not contribute to the viewable
image. This change removes the data which reduces the files in
size so less data needs to be transfered to browsers.

Change-Id: Ifdd96d8178db35225c31237c18365b1e05256c4c
Closes-bug: #1429980

commit_message:
Reinstall postgres and cobbler on container start if needed

Because cobbler and postgres packages are preinstalled before
deployment, their lib dirs will appear empty when mounted as
a container for the first time. This means the cobbler and
postgresql-server packages should be reinstalled.

blueprint stateless-docker-containers

Change-Id: I0b8ec95638f33577f84ca57d127f32d9c1775b19

commit_message:
Backport 94ba3bc to juno

source) to juno branch.  This is required for tempest swift tests to
run successfully with multiple swift_proxy backends behind HAProxy.

commit_message:
fix router schedule in dvr migrate case

Current method get_unscheduled_routers method in
l3_agent_scheduler.py cannot deal with distributed
router schedule. And currently, it will serve
method auto_schedule_routers, and the latter one
will only schedule routers to first L3 agent which
sends sync_routers message to neutron server, we
can find this in neutron cnofig file in comment of
attribute router_auto_schedule.

And that will cause an issue in DVR migration case,
non-DVR env migrate to DVR env case. For example,
in a 1+N env, after DVR migration, not all compute
nodes will be able to create qrouter netns.

We can get distributed routers for a given host,
by checking if any router_interface_distributed
ports are in the same subnets of ports on host.
If those ports exist, related distributed routers
should be scheduled to l3-agent on host.

Closes-Bug: #1423067

Change-Id: I1b66260c7cfbc3b989ad15a1475d680bf8e72375

commit_message:
Fixes ceilometer-compute service start failure

Currently ceilometer-compute service is failing to start in the
'vmware' region, because of the additional parameter 'port', is
added to the oslo.vmware _get_wsdl_loc method.

This patch fixes it by not calling the private method _get_wsdl_loc,
avoiding the mismatch in the method call. Additional optional
'wsdl_location' is added to over-ride to default location for bug
work-arounds.

Test cases are not added, since the changed method just calls the
oslo.vmware and method is already mocked in the setUp of the
class TestVsphereInspectio
Closes-Bug: #1326230

Change-Id: I80dee9bc49b4b55a263529a091177fc768a78faf

HP lefthand driver filter and evalautor function

This patch implements the merged change in the scheduler
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/129987/ in HP lefthand driver.

2. Added 2 stats total_volumes and capacity_utilization so they can be
used as the part of the formula in filter_function or goodness_function
string.

commit_message:
Use RequestSpec object in select_destinations()

Now that there is a RequestSpec object, we can temporarily instantiate it
in the select_destinations() method for each Scheduler driver.
The instantiation will happen in build_request_spec() in a separate patch
series, as it was said in the spec (because it needs to bump a new version
for the Scheduler API)

Partially-Implements: blueprint request-spec-object

Change-Id: I5e5b0cfc4bedc7f55a8006889422ab93e30e2c06

commit_message:
Modify build_request_spec to return NovaObjects for props and type

As we are planning to provide a RequestSpec object for passing over the wire
to the Scheduler, we need to have NovaObjects for the attributes of the spec.

As there is no easy way to create a NovaObject from a complex dict and as
there is no reason to primitive/deprimitive an Object over the wire, then
let's us provide directly the NovaObjects in the spec.

Partially-Implements: blueprint request-spec-object

Change-Id: Ic26f2b7ab662a8910ca50a2bd8b67bed90de8c2a

commit_message:
Do not call Zabbix in case of deletion of cluster

No reason to call Zabbix to report about changes because
we delete node with it few seconds after.

Also fixed:

zabbix error respond may not contain data field

Example:

{ 'jsonrpc': '2.0', 'id': '1', 'error': {
  'message': "Error connecting to database [Can't connect
              to local MySQL server through socket
              '/var/run/mysqld/mysqld.sock' (2)]",
  'code': 1}}

Change-Id: Ia25c7107b3dc535b6e14db74a82d096fd6caa4d0
Closes-Bug: #1419775
(cherry picked from commit 2eee83b38df58e06fa297994efa5f6f19ce65f0a)

commit_message:
Eventlet green threads not released back to pool

Presently, the wsgi server allows persist connections hence even after
the response is sent to the client, it doesn't close the client socket
connection.
Because of this problem, the green thread is not released back to the pool.

In order to close the client socket connection explicitly after the
response is sent and read successfully by the client, you simply have to
set keepalive to False when you create a wsgi server.

DocImpact:
Added wsgi_keep_alive option (default=True).
In order to maintain the backward compatibility, setting wsgi_keep_alive
as True by default. Recommended is set it to False.

Conflicts:
        cinder/wsgi.py
        etc/cinder/cinder.conf.sample

SecurityImpact

Closes-Bug: #1361360
Change-Id: Ic57b2aceb136e8626388cfe4df72b2f47cb0661c
(cherry picked from commit fc87da7eeb3451e139ee71b31095d0b9093332ce)

commit_message:
Remove HAProxy configuration for RabbitMQ

File /etc/haproxy/conf.d/100-rabbitmq.cfg is not used anymore
since all Openstack services Fuel deploys now support Oslo messaging
and rabbit_hosts parameter and is directly connected to AMQP nodes.
Load balancing is not required since we use active/active cluster for
AMQP and all instances of RabbitMQ are active.

Closes-bug: #1421611

Change-Id: I36829b1da352214393dedb2e120f7ba7af19fae2
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobrelia@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
Do not try to stop and reconfigure nova-network on compute nodes

- vmware-compute task tries to stop nova-network service in vCenter
  enabled environment, but fails dur to service absence because it was not
  installed by
  osnailyfacter/modular/openstack-network/openstack-network.pp
- remove vmware-compute task from osnailyfacter/vmware/tasks.yaml
- remove vmware-compute dependency in
  osnailyfacter/modular/openstack-network/tasks.yaml
- delete osnailyfacter/modular/vmware/vmware-compute.pp

Change-Id: I8e71d725ce4c55783f19afde11b509a16542c6f4

for files.

commit_message:
Add crontabs and anacron to rsyslog deps

Closes race condition for rsyslog container
trying to add /etc/cron.daily/anacron before
crontabs package is installed.

Closes-Bug: #1425605

commit_message:
Remove vxlan from default tenant network types

When deployment with VLAN's is selected, and there're no more VLAN to use
for created network, Neutron tries to create a network with VXLAN segmentation,
which is not supported currently. To prevent this behaviour VXLAN is removed
from default tenant network types

Change-Id: Ifa5e5c1c17ccd44c5dba9f6f6c7e3f5df5942cee
Closes-bug: #1423345

commit_message:
Remove vxlan from default tenant network types

When deployment with VLAN's is selected, and there're no more VLAN to use
for created network, Neutron tries to create a network with VXLAN segmentation,
which is not supported currently. To prevent this behaviour VXLAN is removed
from default tenant network types

Change-Id: Ifa5e5c1c17ccd44c5dba9f6f6c7e3f5df5942cee
Closes-bug: #1423345

commit_message:
Added more secure options for SSH daemon. Corrected manifests to pass lint

to 2, added verbose level of logging.  Corrected basic lint problems with
osnailyfacter/example/site.pp and nailgun::host-only. Ported to granular
deployment

commit_message:
Make tests use sha256 as openssl default digest algorithm

The tests previously used md5, which is considered broken,
and distros are starting to disable this in their openssl
builds.

Make the tests use sha256 as the default as a long term
sane alternative that should work on all distros.

This will fix Centos 7, and future proof the tests.

Closes-Bug: #1399498
Change-Id: Ic6cc92e47a318d789db3c3c98c67948eefb51fc2
(cherry picked from commit f4495de5a04b03bbd6773b6b059ea0341a2d0aea)

The tests previously used md5, which is considered broken,
and distros are starting to disable this in their openssl
builds.

commit_message:
Set backend_alg for swift_proxy to source

When making calls to swift-proxy in quick succession, and eventual
consistency, having "leastconn" as default for swift-proxy can cause
unexpected issues. Especially evident when running tempest on a
multinode install.

(cherry picked from commit 94ba3bcbf75e7957e790a5e3b0d3b29de1b3d441)

Conflicts:
	playbooks/vars/configs/haproxy_config.yml

Change-Id: I5cc87c219dab0725eef7fb9a90420623a18496f8
Closes-Bug: #1428081

commit_message:
Disable notifications in Nova and Glance without Ceilometer

Currently, even if Ceilomemter isn't enabled, notifications for the Nova
and Glance services on the controller nodes are enabled. The notification.*
queues are being filled up, but no consumer reads from them.

Glance changes are taken from I3f2c29adbfb605ef288962f72ba81c11811cb35

Change-Id: I00db51ceb4121e73bfe7e256b895e4fae122a496

subject: Fixes agent call may hanged upon action call
revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2015-03-09 08:44:16.000000000', 'files': ['murano/common/engine.py', 'murano/engine/system/agent.py', 'meta/io.murano/Classes/Environment.yaml', 'murano/engine/system/agent_listener.py', 'murano/engine/environment.py', 'murano/tests/unit/dsl/test_agent.py'], 'message': 'Fixes agent call may hanged upon action call

When action called AgentListener automatically starts listening upon
first EP send to the agent. But Environment.deploy() were the only
place where AgentLister was stopped. So when action other than
Environment.deploy() was called there is no one to stop listener.
Thus on each action call new listener on the same RabbitMQ queue
was started causing listeners to steal messages from each other.
Agent.call() that never received response from agent caused
deployment/action hang.

Change-Id: Ia778c816a0e2f57d1f694fd1f128848f61b21a2d
Closes-Bug: #1425963
'}]
commit_message:
Fixes agent call may hanged upon action call

When action called AgentListener automatically starts listening upon
first EP send to the agent. But Environment.deploy() were the only
place where AgentLister was stopped. So when action other than
Environment.deploy() was called there is no one to stop listener.
Thus on each action call new listener on the same RabbitMQ queue
was started causing listeners to steal messages from each other.
Agent.call() that never received response from agent caused
deployment/action hang.

Change-Id: Ia778c816a0e2f57d1f694fd1f128848f61b21a2d
Closes-Bug: #1425963

commit_message:
Split the api controllers and resources

 - Move the v1 controllers to a separate controllers package
 - Split each controller into separate packages
 - Move the v1 resources to a datamodels package
 - Split each resource into separate packages
 - Get the RPC client and RPC target from a global object rather than
   from the request context
 - Changed the base Controller API (breaking change)

Co-Authored-By: Guillaume Espanel <guillaume.espanel@objectif-libre.com>

commit_message:
Fixing permissions for data processing panels

Recently, the data processing service was renamed to
"data-processing" rather than "data_processing".  Each
panel needs to be updated so that it will show up when
the data-processing service is enabled.  Also updated
the underlying test data to reflect the update.

Change-Id: I38d7350215cbe5c5f406d75d6be7c9057957bc69
Closes-Bug:  #1429987

commit_message:
Refactor multiple references to $(document)

According to the Horizon Contributing Guide, we are to:
"Avoid creating instances of the same object repeatedly
within the same scope. Instead, assign the object to a
variable and re-use the existing object."

The guide references the use of "$(document)", as an
example. And yet multiple examples can be found of that
sort of approach. This commit cleans up those references.

Partial-Bug: 1412971
Change-Id: Ica05700101ae9a453623d928f07b75fa7aaca186

If there are no resources associated with a
tenant, it was deleted from Arista DB in
delete_xxx_precommit() methods. The sync
mechanism used to make sure that back-end is in

Lately, the sync mechanism has been enhanced to

delete_tenat() call now needs to be invoked from

'}]
commit_message:
In Arista ML2 delete tenant without any resources

If there are no resources associated with a
tenant, it was deleted from Arista DB in
delete_xxx_precommit() methods. The sync
mechanism used to make sure that back-end is in
sync with DB.

Lately, the sync mechanism has been enhanced to
support scaled deployment. Therefore, the
delete_tenat() call now needs to be invoked from
delete_xxx_postcommit() methods instead of
delete_xxx_precommit() methods. Additionally,
when the tenant is removed from the DB, it is
removed from the back-end as well. This removes
the dependancy on the sync mechanism to take
care of this.
[Note: Sync will still do it, but, this way it
gets done right away]

Closes-bug: 1429968
Change-Id: I2f6ddb01079fe4e2648685ca97d0be06db2d1a55

commit_message:
Not to detach volume which has no connection_info

After failure of attaching volume with RPC problem,
unnecessary block_device_mapping of volume is recorded.
Because of this record, terminate_instance sometimes makes mistakes.
Volume that attached to another instance will be available from in-use.
So, this patch makes not to detach volume that doesn't have connection_info.

Closes-Bug: #1377161

[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-03-08 11:34:58.000000000', 'files': ['ec2api/api/clients.py'], 'message': "Switch to usage of v21 compute API

A preparation step to get rid of Nova DB usage.

Since microversions are supported by v21 only, we must use it in several
cases. But there is no reason to use both (1 and 2.1) versions
simultaneously. Therefore we use v21 for all requests.

If we will support deployments with no v21 api service, we will decide
which version to use at run time and specify it at one place instead of
do this for each call. Therefore we don't need service_type parameter

Mandatory specification of the required microversion seems preffered at

of time (24s vs 47.5s for all unit tests). So we've omitted them.

Change-Id: Ia5f5ba88a10614e14e8d0520e8e9e4df1f5bccd2
"}]
commit_message:
Switch to usage of v21 compute API

A preparation step to get rid of Nova DB usage.

Since microversions are supported by v21 only, we must use it in several
cases. But there is no reason to use both (1 and 2.1) versions
simultaneously. Therefore we use v21 for all requests.

If we will support deployments with no v21 api service, we will decide
which version to use at run time and specify it at one place instead of
do this for each call. Therefore we don't need service_type parameter
for an interface of nova client initialization function.

Mandatory specification of the required microversion seems preffered at
the moment, because it increases nova compute output for necessary cases
only.

Client extenstions aren't used now, but their initialization take a lot
of time (24s vs 47.5s for all unit tests). So we've omitted them.

Also correct way to initialize client attributes is used.

Change-Id: Ia5f5ba88a10614e14e8d0520e8e9e4df1f5bccd2

commit_message:
requirements-rpm.txt: remove redundant entries

yumdownloader picks the dependencies on its own, hence listing them in
requirements-rpm.txt has no effect (except making ISO build slower)

- apr{,-util} (dependencies of httpd)
- boost-program-options (galera, ceph-test, mongodb, qpid-qmf)
- boost-system (qemu, ceph, mongodb, openstack-cinder, cloud-utils)
- boost-thread (qemu, ceph, cloud-utils, mongodb, openstack-nova)
- libcephfs1 (ceph, ceph-test)
- libicu (mongodb, nodejs, ceph, gdisk, v8)
- libfcgi (ceph-radosgw, fcgiwrap)
- libqb (pacemaker, crmsh)
- librados2 (qemu, ceph, cloud-utils, python-cinder)
- librbd1 (qemu, ceph, openstack-nva, cloud-utils)
- librepl (rsyslog)
- libselinux-ruby (puppet)
- libudev (qemu, ceph, crmsh, docker-io, fence-agents, parted, pacemaker)
- libunwind (ceph, mongodb)
- libuv (nodejs)
- libyaml, lots of packages depends on it (hiera, PyYAML, neutron, sahara, ...)
- mtools (cobbler, syslinux)

Change-Id: I2787bdbfb22c0ffdbdaff802633a6b11f732b0ce

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-03-05 22:45:41.000000000', 'files': ['neutron/tests/unit/test_attributes.py', 'neutron/api/v2/attributes.py'], 'message': 'attributes: Additional IP address validation

Introduce an additional IP address validation instead of assuming
that netaddr provides it.  Namely, it ensures that an address
either has ':' (IPv6) or 3 periods like 'xx.xx.xx.xx'. (IPv4)

The "'1' * 59" test case recently introduced by
commit 1681f62ec91b6c3705a14393815542dc1746de71 fails on
some platforms because it's considered a valid address by
their inet_aton.  Examples of such platforms: NetBSD, OS X

While one might argue it's a fault of the platforms, this is

commit_message:
attributes: Additional IP address validation

Introduce an additional IP address validation instead of assuming
that netaddr provides it.  Namely, it ensures that an address
either has ':' (IPv6) or 3 periods like 'xx.xx.xx.xx'. (IPv4)

The "'1' * 59" test case recently introduced by
commit 1681f62ec91b6c3705a14393815542dc1746de71 fails on
some platforms because it's considered a valid address by
their inet_aton.  Examples of such platforms: NetBSD, OS X

While one might argue it's a fault of the platforms, this is
a historical behavior which is probably too late to change there.

(The breakage has been hidden by later UT changes in
commit 35662d07628452d14306f5197871ad64f6396ff3 .
This commit includes a UT change to uncover the problem again.)

(cherry-picked from 2794bb89d664355ae1194a0b1f8346c1538caef8)
Closes-Bug: #1394867
Related-Bug: #1378450
Change-Id: Ibe02f8b7c4d437bf7abbe7304ca138bdcf4bfdb9

Refactor test_parser module

test_parser.py file is now over 4,000 lines. It won't be an easy task
for maintenance. After the split, contributors can work on smaller files
independently, for example, to replace mox with mock.

commit_message:
Move OSC auth plugins so they can be found

The plugin detection at the top of openstackclient.api.auth did not
detect the plugins at the bottom of that file because, surprise,
they had not been declared yet so the entry points were ignored.

Move both plugin subclasses into openstackclient.api.auth_plugin.

Fix a problem with the password callback that was otherwise made
worse with this change.

Closes-Bug: 1428912
Change-Id: Idc3b72534071e0013c8922884a8bc14137509a0f

subject: Paging backward in Image table should handle same timestamp images
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-03-09 01:43:45.000000000', 'files': ['openstack_dashboard/dashboards/admin/images/views.py'], 'message': 'Paging backward in Image table should handle same timestamp images

Currently paging backward is broken when handling the the images
with same timestamp. This is because the image view has reverse sorted
the image based on the create_at timestamp. This is unnecessary because
the order has been sorted correctly when we issue the glace api (image_list_detailed).

This fix is to take out the sorting process in the IndexView but using a
simple reverse method instead. This will ensure the order is correct.

Change-Id: I41e04b2ffb228fa98a10ecd71d3e1474b3580658
Closes-Bug: #1427014
'}]
commit_message:
Paging backward in Image table should handle same timestamp images

Currently paging backward is broken when handling the the images
with same timestamp. This is because the image view has reverse sorted
the image based on the create_at timestamp. This is unnecessary because
the order has been sorted correctly when we issue the glace api (image_list_detailed).

This fix is to take out the sorting process in the IndexView but using a
simple reverse method instead. This will ensure the order is correct.

Change-Id: I41e04b2ffb228fa98a10ecd71d3e1474b3580658
Closes-Bug: #1427014

commit_message:
Pulling in tempest files

Lbaas v2 tempests tests need a stable version of tempest to import
from.  Simply importing tempest is not an option as trunk changes
rapidly.  Pulling the tempest files into tree is needed to complete
stable tests.  This method follows the process neutron plans to take.
In the future, the v1 tempest tests will also be pulled into tree and
these files will need to be updated, or completely removed if the
tempest tests are modified to just import neutron's tempest clone
or if tempest-lib has everything needed.

Change-Id: Id7f37f3a7194c0eabd930cac0b2efda6c5ffb52c

valueMeta for measurements that have it will be received in the message
from Kakfa and then persisted

https://review.openstack.org/160654

commit_message:
Add measurement valueMeta

valueMeta for measurements that have it will be sent in the message
to Kakfa. valueMeta for measurements that have it will be returned
when the measurement is read

Supported only by Influx V8 for now

Requires the changes to monasca-common from
https://review.openstack.org/160654

Removed ability to send arrays of timestamps and values. It was
undocumented and unused

commit_message:
Fix ironic port-create deprecated option

A recent ironicclient commit If05d51b09d787ccfbf6f6d35d8e752d42f673601

commit_message:
Compute: Catch binding failed exception while init host

While compute starts it will init all instances,
if an exception is raised from one instance
(e.g NovaException during plug_vifs), then the
compute process exits unexpectedly because of
this unhandled exception.
This commit changes the NovaException to more
appropriate VirtualInterfacePlugException and
catches it during init host, as well as the
instance is set to error state, with this change
the compute process can be started normally even
if this VirtualInterfacePlugException is raised.

Closes-bug: #1324041

Conflicts:
	nova/tests/unit/compute/test_compute_mgr.py

Change-Id: Ia584dba66affb86787e3069df19bd17b89cb5c49
(cherry picked from commit 16ac50b1e760b7d20b840763b271a497b66ad5a5)

commit_message:
fix the value of samples_cnt to advoid to be zero

code before:
VC_REAL_TIME_SAMPLING_INTERVAL = 20

samples_cnt = (int(duration / VC_REAL_TIME_SAMPLING_INTERVAL)
if duration else 1)
query_spec.maxSample = samples_cnt

if we set the value of "interval" in /etc/ceilometer/pipline.yaml to less
than 20,the value of "samples_cnt" will be 0.

if we set the value of "interval" in /etc/ceilometer/pipline.yaml to less
than 20,the value of "samples_cnt" will be 0,which will cause problem in
below code:

stat_value = float(sum(metric_series.value)) / samples_cnt

Change-Id: I18353b1d36273b3f087b923db7cd3a861538e4c0
Closes-Bug:#1415307

commit_message:
None in config choices breaks oslo-config-generator

Tempest using StrOpt with choices
choices=[None, 'normal', 'direct', 'macvtap']

And oslo-config-generator does not like it. We need to
print "<None>" when we encounter None as a choice.

commit_message:
Remove support for 3.3

We don't test against 3.3 in the integrated CI anymore
so we likely shouldn't say that we support it anymore
since it's not something we are guaranteeing.

We still support 3.4 (and that's what we are testing
against so we retain that version in the setup.cfg
file).

commit_message:
Prevent premature evaluation of Sliding Window

Added ability to configure how long thresh should wait for metrics
before showing up before evaluating sliding window. Ensure the
current time is past the end of the sliding window plus the delay
before sliding

Only evaluate SubAlarm if current time is past slot end timestamp

This change depends on the monasca-common changes of
https://review.openstack.org/161941

Change-Id: Iab7cb1580253f2fc7c114cfb95c009dba6b23331

commit_message:
Bare Metal Trust Using Intel TXT

This provides a trust boot solution, to determine the node
is trusted or not after deployed with Ironic, leveraging
Intel TXT to measure BIOS, Option ROM and Kernel/Ramdisk.
Talk and Demo:
https://www.openstack.org/summit/openstack-paris-summit-2014/
session-videos/presentation/trusted-bare-metal-what-and-39-s-that
Co-Authored-By: Bhandaru, Malini K <malini.k.bhandaru@intel.com>
Change-Id: I046030cc42f943435ec6fc078c31228c1b22bd99

commit_message:
Add support to incremental backups in cinder

1. Added a new option to create backup to support incremental backups.
   New CLI option added for "cinder backup": --incremental or --incr
   By default, it is full backup.
   Add the following to API: 'incremental': True or False
   (False is the default)
2. swift.py creates sha256file for every backup to calculate deltas

DocImpact
APIImpact
Co-Authored-By: Xing Yang <xing.yang@emc.com>
Implements: blueprint incremental-backup
Change-Id: I98f3765f7afa47bda6a8c7004f809c3cc4d1bd4b

commit_message:
WIP: partially fix the bug of live-migration with config drive

In current version of nova, live-migration with config drive on
local disk is forbbiden due to the bug of libvirt of copying readonly
disk.

However, if we use vfat as the format of config drive,
the function of live-migration works well.

In this patch, we re-open the function of live-migration to admin users.
Notice you should add 'config_drive_format = vfat' in nova.conf explicitly.

This patch doesn't solve the problem fundamentally which need further
efforts, but offers a simple and feasible solution to user.

Change-Id: Iee7c27d690b4a2513bbe563faa6c7b34f290b942
Partial-Bug: #1246201

commit_message:
SemVer utility to store object versions in DB

Adds an utility which may convert Version objects (provided by
semantic_version library) into a combination of long 64-bit integer
value and two preformatted strings. If stored in the database these
values unambiguously define object precedence according to semver
notation. This may be used for correct ordering of database queries.

Adds a class which is compatible with SQLAlchemy composite field, so one
may use it directly in SQLAlchemy object models to define version fields
and query the database.

Needed for Artifacts model

Depends-on: I74c00625634f246a96a1a9db4e6ff4335e649404

Implements-blueprint: semver-support

Change-Id: I33212ea92cca50a143b9141f8147f7db27bb9e7c

commit_message:
Partial revert of putting bare-metal in repo roles

Bug https://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/ironic/+bug/1429962
in ubuntu repo will cause our repo tests to fail.
To allow progress while this gets fixed, pulling bare-metal
conductor from the os-compute-worker role.

The other bare-metal patches for the cookbook should also get in to
allow clean tests to be run.

Related-Bug: #1429245

commit_message:
Set umask to 0022 for OCF scripts that add network namespaces

When ns_haproxy or ns_IPaddr2 create the first network namespace
/var/run/netns will have permissions of 751 due to the umask
being 0026 at that time. This will cause the problems with
Neutron agents described in the referenced bug.

Change-Id: Ib8d1f485272ef843e935f43b1b40d7db6b0c2e78
Closes-bug: #1414239

commit_message:
Trim ansible's output to console.log

Since I2786f73334b99bfa98d344c50337c86f75fae273 ansible's output is
logged properly to a file and published at the end of a gate check.
This trims the output from ansible to the console to make the console
log that is published far shorter and easier to read.

revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-03-03 15:50:59.000000000', 'files': ['global-requirements.txt', 'cap.py'], 'message': "Restore minimum requirement version for kombu

Commit 499db6b64071c2afa16390ad2bc024e6a96db4ff capped anything that
didn't have an upper bound for stable/juno using what was currently

However, it pinned kombu at 3.0.7 when it was >= 2.5.0 before which

commit_message:
Restore minimum requirement version for kombu

Commit 499db6b64071c2afa16390ad2bc024e6a96db4ff capped anything that
didn't have an upper bound for stable/juno using what was currently
tested in the gate from pip-freeze output.

However, it pinned kombu at 3.0.7 when it was >= 2.5.0 before which
breaks anyone that's already shipped a Juno-based distribution with the
level of packages required in the last release (2014.2.2).

This change restores the lower bound on kombu and makes 3.0.7 the upper
bound but not the only required version.

Going through the other == pins in commit 499db6b64 the only other one
is suds but it pins on what was already the minimum required version,
0.4, so that was OK.

Change-Id: I8bb1c2a752156271a88b832863b1b6fc26e61e7f

commit_message:
Fixed issues while using --bypass-url

Python-troveclient 1.0.8 introduced a regression where the usage
of --bypass-url results in an AuthSystemNotFound exception.
Removing some redundant code, which was due to a previous merge
conflict, fixed the issue.

Closes-bug 1416120

Change-Id: I1c949f69ee08447ce88aeefa92c60f361ab54832

commit_message:
Make service_create return 400 with invalid json manifest

Currently when service_create is passed an invalid
json formatted manifest, 500 status is returned
to user due to unhandled ValueError exception.
This patch handles this exception and return 400
status to user when invalid manifest is passed.

Change-Id: I8a4b7ab9217947b56db625c66164c19865f113fc
Closes-bug: #1429757

subject: Fix bash autocompletion of "rally task sla_check"
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-03-09 20:10:52.000000000', 'files': ['rally/cmd/cliutils.py', 'etc/rally.bash_completion'], 'message': 'Fix bash autocompletion of "rally task sla_check"

Character "_" is used as delimiter of commands and
their subcommands stored in bash array as keys,
i.e. in form "task_sla_check". Current code splits
it into an array based on delimiter "_" which would
return array with three values - task, sla and check.
The patch takes first value from the beginning to
first "_" as command and the rest as its subcommand.

Change-Id: I7d8c9b1eeb7c28ef24b0f2f366c6a18930282be5
Closes-bug: 1401180
'}]
commit_message:
Fix bash autocompletion of "rally task sla_check"

Character "_" is used as delimiter of commands and
their subcommands stored in bash array as keys,
i.e. in form "task_sla_check". Current code splits
it into an array based on delimiter "_" which would
return array with three values - task, sla and check.
The patch takes first value from the beginning to
first "_" as command and the rest as its subcommand.

Change-Id: I7d8c9b1eeb7c28ef24b0f2f366c6a18930282be5
Closes-bug: 1401180

commit_message:
Add test_sahara_create_delete_job_binary test method

Adding test method that checks creating/removal of job binary under
Project/Data Processing/Job Binaries.
The core testing function can be easily extended with other job binary
templates; the initial versions allows to test for jobs stored on the
Internal DB.

As part of this test several items have been created
* new pageobject class JobbinariesPage
* new form field FileInputFormFieldRegion

commit_message:
Create and upload heat test images to tarballs

This change will only create a fedora image but a future change could
also generate images for Ubuntu and CentOS7.

build-heat-test-image.sh requires an installed diskimage-builder,
so the recipe for diskimage-builder-install was determined by running
build-heat-test-image.sh in a pristine trusty cloud image.

Change-Id: I03a9efe47fc3f21471a57e33ab09b0d7a13b219c

Bump glance_store to 0.2.0

Version 0.2.0 glance_store library has content that glance server
plans on leveraging. The release adds support for store capabilities
as enabled by glance blueprint store-capabilities (Change
I7cc3756535d09a6804ba02a23c86af13b8e9cd1a ) and helps us bump up the version here.

commit_message:
Include readonly flag in metadef API

Current API does not return readonly flag for properties included when
querying for metadef namespaces. The readonly field is included in both
the spec and the schema definition, so it should be returned in API
results as well.

DocImpact
APIImpact

Change-Id: I0db4491e8b44c8aa591a21fd95c7a0713bff9d4c
Closes-Bug: 1406235

commit_message:
Eventlet green threads not released back to pool

Presently, the wsgi server allows persist connections. Hence even after
the response is sent to the client, it doesn't close the client socket
connection. Because of this problem, the green thread is not released
back to the pool.

In order to close the client socket connection explicitly after the
response is sent and read successfully by the client, you simply have to
set keepalive to False when you create a wsgi server.

DocImpact:
Added http_keepalive option (default=True).

SecurityImpact

Closes-Bug: #1361360
Change-Id: I93aaca24935a4f3096210233097dd6b8c5440176

subject: Disable gate-oslo-incubator-python34 for Icehouse
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-03-04 16:32:50.000000000', 'files': ['zuul/layout.yaml'], 'message': 'Disable gate-oslo-incubator-python34 for Icehouse

The job was broken by recent switch from py33 to py34 jobs. Precise
images do not contain latest python version, and fail now.

As per oslo team,

"The incubator python 3 job was added to help us port incubated code to
python 3 before graduating it. We won't be graduating modules from the
stable branch, so as long as none of the consuming projects have python
3 jobs on their stable branches we can just drop the icehouse python 3
job for oslo-incubator."

I don't know of any consumers that actually use code from oslo-incubator
and at the same time support py3, so disabling the job for the branch.

Change-Id: Ia8f5fac1d37a0ce8062ba144da9c3adcf9a474a3
'}]
commit_message:
Disable gate-oslo-incubator-python34 for Icehouse

The job was broken by recent switch from py33 to py34 jobs. Precise
images do not contain latest python version, and fail now.

As per oslo team,

"The incubator python 3 job was added to help us port incubated code to
python 3 before graduating it. We won't be graduating modules from the
stable branch, so as long as none of the consuming projects have python
3 jobs on their stable branches we can just drop the icehouse python 3
job for oslo-incubator."

I don't know of any consumers that actually use code from oslo-incubator
and at the same time support py3, so disabling the job for the branch.

Change-Id: Ia8f5fac1d37a0ce8062ba144da9c3adcf9a474a3

commit_message:
Replacing data_processing with data-processing

Using data_processing when setting keystone static catalog causes
Sahara not to find the endpoint afterwards since keystone translates
data_processing to data-processing.

Change-Id: I5b253e4f5a0486913c59150d2bafd631f06a8cf1

commit_message:
Add tests for subprocesses and deserialization

- Add a new section "shell_injection" to the config file.
- Read subprocess functions from config in "injection_shell.py".
- Check all process-starting calls in "injection_wildcard.py".
- Avoid double-counting of subprocess.Popen(shell=True) and others.
- Check for cPickle and marshal.
- Don't flag `pickle.dumps`, since `import pickle` triggers a message.
- Update a handful of examples and tests.

Change-Id: I041c7d8a30658b177e88d1664bb9dcf08367d7f7

commit_message:

into a common type, by pulling package installation and database
configuration into the job runtime. It also adds an experimental job
to test-drive these features.

commit_message:
Unify using six.moves.range rename everywhere

Mainly to improve consistency, use range() from six.moves
renames across glance.

Behaves consistently like py2 xrange() and py3 range().

Removes unnecessary range() from glace/api/v2/images.py

Change-Id: Id21f923d05600b902f2239e25ef01716c07e74a3

commit_message:
Propose projects.yaml normalization daily

Add a job that will propose a change (or update a change) to
normalize projects.yaml, and run it once daily.  Normalization,
in this case, chiefly means removing un-used upstream lines
from projects.yaml (but will also catch minor YAML errors and
line wrapping).

Also simplify the proposal node regex.

commit_message:
Create our own rally job for ec2-api

In previous review
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/159138/
I tried to use existing rally job. But I skipped fact that in this job
ec2-api wouldn't loaded. Now I was trying to think up how this existing
job can be adapted to load ec2-api plugin. And simple way to do it -
is to create another job-template with needed shell script and needed params.

Change-Id: I3a95b298a70795601ef4002fc413e91960af0f2b

commit_message:
Remove support for 3.3

We don't test against 3.3 in the integrated CI anymore
so we likely shouldn't say that we support it anymore
since it's not something we are guaranteeing.

We still support 3.4 (and that's what we are testing
against so we use that version in the setup.cfg
file).

Change-Id: I9fadcac92ea3f43e811818cf013f93445ec1b5e9

The domain API has moved to the resource manager. While there are

commit_message:
'Assignment' has no attr 'get_domain_by_name'

The domain API has moved to the resource manager. While there are
redirects at the manager level so that most calls won't notice,
keystone-manage mapping_purge is making a direct driver call (bypassing
the manager). It needs to be updated to point to the resource manager
rather than the assignment manager.

Change-Id: Ia4fc89a0496bf9dc45300dbbe4cb776210340de4
Closes-Bug: 1427379

commit_message:
Add packaging for Docker containers

In order to safely package containers, yum update -y
was added to each container.
Containers are now built and stored in an archive,
which is packed into a new rpm fuel-docker-images.

blueprint package-docker-images

Change-Id: Ib583e41ec07c9d60eb993216c00ef2f0ba2ca110

commit_message:
Agent configuration and BIND9 improvements

* Make sure BIND9 rndc addzone/delzone compatiblity is maintained
by stripping the trailing dot on zone names
* Write out non-relativized zone files
* Add a transfer-source option to the Agent for AXFRs
* Add a query-destination option to the Agent BIND9 Backend
* Remove the 1 second sleep, as the Pool Manager should be able to recover

Change-Id: Ief7483d477affd17a13139f591dfe94be8285b74

commit_message:
Print instance UUID to log

This macro allows a job running on a cloud-based instance to print the
UUID of that instance to the build log.  By the time it is determined
that a test failed due to a system or networking error, the instance
has already been deleted.  The UUID can be used to locate the physical
system the instance ran on so that analysis can be done at that level.
By providing it in the build log, users will not have to find someone
with access to the nodepool logs to get this level of support for this
type of issue.

Depends-On: Ib84ec30b5c4c5de5d5be80cae2b4230c1aba3bc6
Change-Id: Iddcd56e2e2f2a942573a9868d1c009106b38564a

commit_message:
Add gate-tempest-dsvm-full-trove

Because trove builds on the compute base layer, it does not need
to be tested in all devstack-gate tests.  Instead, create a new
job that tests trove in a devstack environment as a first step
in removing it from the standard configuration.

Specify that TROVE should be enabled in the devstack updown job
so that the parts that enable trove are exercised in devstack.
This is already currently the case, but this updates the job config
so that it will continue to do so later when we remove trove from
the default config.

Change-Id: Ib503e45b08edfb2252d7c56af14f97d630e137d8

commit_message:
Add fuel-centos-build container for fuel/centos

fuel/centos will now be built from CentOS6
container dynamically with current package set
instead of being periodically rebuilt. It uses
ami-creator, which only runs on CentOS. It is
run inside Docker so it can be used on an
Ubuntu build host. After the image is created,
img2docker loads the content into Docker as a
Docker image.

Consolidates save/load to a single archive
instead of rolling up separate container tar
files.

Note that fuel-centos.done target depends on
RPM package build to avoid race conditions
where repo metadata is updated while base image
is being built.

Change-Id: I62abc07e79847b5c69eaa1a983575b214ebed649
Closes-Bug: #1336911

We need to modify the column name to stay consistent.

commit_message:
Deprecate passing "extras" in token data

The "extras" attribute in v3 was introduced to copy a bug in v2 which
leaked an implementation detail of the SQL backend (the "extras" column)
into token responses. I can't find any evidence that this has ever been
useful (or used) in v3.

bp: deprecated-as-of-kilo
Change-Id: I4c1162b39d0f5c29069ec06921a69cddb70c041b

revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2015-03-09 15:48:30.000000000', 'files': ['nova_powervm/tests/virt/powervm/disk/test_ssp.py', 'nova_powervm/virt/powervm/driver.py', 'nova_powervm/tests/virt/powervm/data/fake_ssp.txt', 'nova_powervm/virt/powervm/__init__.py', 'nova_powervm/virt/powervm/disk/ssp.py', 'nova_powervm/tests/virt/powervm/test_driver.py', 'nova_powervm/virt/powervm/disk/__init__.py', 'nova_powervm/virt/powervm/disk/localdisk.py'], 'message': 'SSP storage driver: _fetch_ssp_wrap()

Helper method _fetch_ssp_wrap() for the new SSPDiskAdapter driver.
Fetches the requested SharedStoragePool and returns it wrapped in an SSP
EntryWrapper.  Operates in three modes:

1) On driver startup, performs REST API search to locate the SSP based
on the name defined in the configuration.

2) On subsequent invocations, performs a REST API read with etag.
   a) If etag matched, returns cached previously-fetched wrapper.
   b) If etag mismatch, wraps and returns the newly-fetched entry.

Change-Id: I13cba0bd194ae5967e88c82f5ff4fb068786585b
'}]
commit_message:
SSP storage driver: _fetch_ssp_wrap()

Helper method _fetch_ssp_wrap() for the new SSPDiskAdapter driver.
Fetches the requested SharedStoragePool and returns it wrapped in an SSP
EntryWrapper.  Operates in three modes:

1) On driver startup, performs REST API search to locate the SSP based
on the name defined in the configuration.

2) On subsequent invocations, performs a REST API read with etag.
   a) If etag matched, returns cached previously-fetched wrapper.
   b) If etag mismatch, wraps and returns the newly-fetched entry.

Change-Id: I13cba0bd194ae5967e88c82f5ff4fb068786585b

commit_message:
Added option to allow sample expiration more frequently

Added a new CLI param - sql-expire-samples-only
to ceilometer-expirer. This will allow the
expirer to expire samples only, since samples
have more volume and velocity, thus allowing
sample expiration more frequently than other
metering data (meters, resources and metadata).

DocImpact

Closes-Bug: #1424871

Change-Id: I9b3081a3bcc1a24dd7ad7706e76a886af7185af4

commit_message:
Fixing up job binary creation in data processing

Fixing up the job binary creation form so that it can be used
as a target for add_item_link in a DynamicChoiceField.  Also,
making adding items possible from the job creation form for
both mains and libraries.

Partial-Implements: blueprint data-processing-rework-ui

commit_message:
Always show stack status reason in topology

Currently, only when the stack is in error status, the stack status
reason will be displayed, otherwise, there will be two line with
exactly same words, and this makes the enduser confuse. So fixes
this by changing to not show anything when stack in not in error
status.

Change-Id: Ifcd8def6b452ecccef9a8daa0e31504cffa2d6ad
Closes-bug: #1428580

Replace RPC topic-based service queries with binary-based in scheduler

This makes the nova/scheduler subtree query for compute services by
binary name instead of RPC topic.

commit_message:
Implement create_and_upload_volume_to_image scenario for Cinder

The `create_and_upload_volume_to_image' sceanario can not be run
on the DSVM gate with the default settings because it uses 1GB
Swift backend for Glance image store.

commit_message:
Default route missing for IPv6 subnets in HA Router

In an HA setup, keepalived would configure the default gateway (in the master
HA router) by parsing the "virtual_routes" section of keepalived.conf file.
The "virtual_routes" section is properly constructed for an IPv4 subnet, but
requires a minor change for IPv6 subnets.

Conflicts:
    neutron/agent/l3_ha_agent.py
    neutron/tests/functional/agent/test_l3_agent.py

Closes-Bug: #1414937
Change-Id: I54070e048577292d98d86fcc9ca8b9d3e72b4ebe

commit_message:
Base dashboard Jasmine framework

Establishes Jasmine testing features in openstack_dashboard, similar
to the features in horizon. These features allow components specific
to openstack_dashboard to be tested.

Partially Implements: blueprint launch-instance-redesign

Change-Id: I1f996e97f5cd01c9c32d7874eb5c0668d67e24bd

commit_message:
Fix subnet delete issue when vpnservice is associated to it

session.delete(subnet) is failing, if the subnet is associated
to a vpn service.

This patch fixes the issue by raising 'vpnaas.SubnetInUseByVPNService'
exception.

Change-Id: I24beb527e7e3665ebe323411155d2d8c457b6f82
Closes-bug: #1386648

Call show() if the attributes in the PUT are empty

This patch calls the show method if the resources are
updated with empty attributes

Also modified a unit test case in the nec/test_packet_filter
accordingly

Closes-bug: #1366067

commit_message:
Refactor agent iscsi deploy out of pxe driver

This commit refactors the continue_deploy method
in pxe.VendorPassthru.  This takes the agent
iscsi deploy part out of pxe driver so that it
can be reused in other drivers (like iscsi_ilo).

Change-Id: I39d0120d8e7aa02b7f244de9a4d193b8c1666ebe

commit_message:
Switch from qemu to qemu-img on Fedora

On Fedora, qemu is a metapackage which installs all of qemu components,
meaning all the architecture hypervisors.

Since all we need is qemu-img, just ask for it instead.

Change-Id: I2954221520a28f572b1101664513833ceca9fbbd

commit_message:
Fixes for node_visitor, sql and hardcoded password tests

- Fixed node visitor so it doesn't test against docstrings
- fixed a bug in sql injection tests which prevented detection
  of SQL injection issues in function calls
- Re-enabled hardcoded password check, and updated functional test
- Changed hardcoded password from WARN to INFO

Change-Id: I289a158f6f204a5a3c6aad3cd954f051aabb0400

commit_message:
Trim ansible's output to console.log

Since I2786f73334b99bfa98d344c50337c86f75fae273 ansible's output is
logged properly to a file and published at the end of a gate check.
This trims the output from ansible to the console to make the console
log that is published far shorter and easier to read.

Co-Authored-By: Ian Cordasco <ian.cordasco@rackspace.com>
Change-Id: I98fb57a56c1b7ddd6558e265cf6e65b159a05123
Partial-bug: 1425482
(cherry picked from commit a9244537d62662ab3342d1c1bdb74e3b1f23ad0e)

commit_message:
Fix some straggling uses of passing context to remotable methods in tests

We are on a path to remove the implicit context argument for remotable methods
when we move to oslo.versiondobjects (o.vo). In the process of doing a POC for
nova using o.vo, I discovered a few straggling cases where we still depend on
that in the tests.

Related to blueprint kilo-objects

Change-Id: I0dda2aca4dc8c30166f2a576864fe2ab2009a77a

commit_message:
Raise error upon deleting subnet with router ports

Fixes an issue where SLAAC and DHCPV6-stateless subnets can be
deleted even if they are attached to an internal router port.
This patch raises an exception whenever a subnet is deleted
that has existing IP Allocations on an internal router port.

Change-Id: I0a16156274b5736236654fca6700ef2d67f4519b
Closes-Bug: #1424760

commit_message:
Add extraroute contrib plugin

This change installs the extraroute contrib plugin for heat. It also
adds the plugin_dirs option to heat.conf, which defines
the locations where Heat plugins can be installed. The plugin
installation task has been changed to use setup.py instead of pip
because heat contrib plugins do not work with pip (see bug #1428879).

Change-Id: Ifa5167e9d09aa040c381c6870c4856b6f1c4906e
Closes-Bug: #1420346

commit_message:
Prevent premature evaluation of Sliding Window

Add method to determine if current time is past slot end timestamp

Allow a delay to be configured to allow time for metrics to be
recieved. Otherwise, metrics were being discarded if they didn't
arrive immediately

Moved some tests to their proper location

commit_message:
Fall back to generated snmp password with --no-undercloud

Running devtest_overcloud.sh via devtest with --no-undercloud seems
to result in some puppet errors recently, due to the zero-length
password in the heiradata key.

So instead of passing a zero length password, fall back to generating
one in the event no password is found via the undercloud key of the
test environment.

Change-Id: Ia5f9fff1ea3b50f372489a42647e3f47bc219df8
Closes-Bug: #1428726

subject: Add + use read/write lock decorators
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-03-09 05:22:52.000000000', 'files': ['taskflow/storage.py', 'taskflow/utils/lock_utils.py'], 'message': 'Add + use read/write lock decorators

For when a whole function should be locked by
a read or write lock it is quite useful to have
decorators that acquire and release and wrap
the target function with the provided lock.

This change switches the storage module to use
these decorators where appropriate (mainly in
places where the read or write lock is activated
for the duration of the functions call, at which
point it is clearer to just use the new decorators
instead).

Change-Id: I70d2c1ab478e9b7da9446482a4ffb28f6f5227b7
'}]
commit_message:
Add + use read/write lock decorators

For when a whole function should be locked by
a read or write lock it is quite useful to have
decorators that acquire and release and wrap
the target function with the provided lock.

This change switches the storage module to use
these decorators where appropriate (mainly in
places where the read or write lock is activated
for the duration of the functions call, at which
point it is clearer to just use the new decorators
instead).

Change-Id: I70d2c1ab478e9b7da9446482a4ffb28f6f5227b7

commit_message:
Rename volume driver to volume adapter

The role of nova with cinder volumes is to connect the volume to the
backing fabric type.  The original name of volume driver was creating
confusion with the 'Cinder Volume Driver'.

This rename should reduce some confusion by changing the name in nova to
'volume adapter'.

Change-Id: I2ccf1b13e9cb5ddb385e3f42b9f9c43d77260b37

commit_message:
Move WWPN generation into volume connector

PowerVM has multiple strategies to connect Fibre Channel volumes to the
Virtual Machine.  These are generally either vSCSI or NPIV.

These two strategies require the use of different WWPNs upon building
the connector.

If NPIV - the WWPNs are used from the Virtual FC Adapter.
If vSCSI - the WWPNs are used from the host Virtual I/O Server(s)

This change set moves the WWPN generation for the OpenStack volume
connector down into the volume driver itself.

Change-Id: I068909f29918ccd7323d665d5b451f7cfd7d4cc5

commit_message:
Use keystonemiddleware instead of client

The auth_token middleware that lives in
keystoneclient.middleware.auth_token has been deprecated in favour of
keystonemiddleware.auth_token.

This prints a deprecation warning and means we are not getting new
features.

Closes-Bug: #1428376
Change-Id: If5352801b8105533600965a25f02a577a858f1a2

commit_message:
Split out the dir helping functions into a shared helper

In order to allow for the directory/file based backend
to provide a more robust storage object in the near future
we need to start refactoring the common functionality that
such a layer would need; extracting what exists from the
connection object and making it better.

commit_message:
Rename the timing listeners to duration listeners

These listeners really only capture duration (from
when the task started, to when it stopped) and are
not really associated with the time a task started
or when it stopped so we should rename these to be
more appropriatly named.

Change-Id: I54ea0fa739fcea0b3e3c155dc38ce49adfc3bb01
