revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-03-05 15:57:54.000000000', 'files': ['swift/obj/server.py'], 'message': 'Ssync fix for EC PUT path

The recent multi-phase PUT patch calls set_hundred_continue_response_headers()
on wsgi_input regarldess of whether a multi-phase PUT is happening.  Ssync
uses a FileLikeIter for wsgi_input when updating files so pukes on this call.

I believe the right fix is to simply not make the call unless you are doing
multi-phase as defined by the header.

Change-Id: Ia3354cdfd9c3049c3568e4cffbe2c853d8c108bd
'}]
commit_message:
Ssync fix for EC PUT path

The recent multi-phase PUT patch calls set_hundred_continue_response_headers()
on wsgi_input regarldess of whether a multi-phase PUT is happening.  Ssync
uses a FileLikeIter for wsgi_input when updating files so pukes on this call.

I believe the right fix is to simply not make the call unless you are doing
multi-phase as defined by the header.

Change-Id: Ia3354cdfd9c3049c3568e4cffbe2c853d8c108bd

commit_message:
Make baymodel-create fail when no argument passed

This patch lets baymodel-create command fail when
no argument is passed. This makes '--keypair-id'
and '--external-network-id' mandatory arguments
for the command. Also added test cases for it.

Change-Id: I9d0ce412b6924da991b584822aaf3f4060a9f3dc
Closes-bug: #1423038

Fix package version number

update of the BASH_REMATCH references was needed.

This commit updates them.

Use condition context manager instead of acquire/release

manager instead of doing acquire, try, finally, release to
achieve the same thing.

commit_message:
Add a section for "Upgrade Implications"

Some specs recently have included changes that could impact upgrades
(upgradability). Also some recent patch sets have proposed changes
that could have implications for upgrade. To recognize these and help
draw attention to these during the spec review process, I propose the
addition of a section for Upgrade Implications. The specification
template has been updated to reflect this.

This change has no (adverse) upgrade implications.

Change-Id: Iab2a399b7c85b9ddae0c8ae73db9a5da6374203d

commit_message:
WIP Change init_l3 args for multi-prefix

This modifies the arguments to init_l3() to match the changes made
in the L3 Agent Linux driver as part of the multiple-ipv6-prefixes
blueprint.

The init_l3() method is changed to accept a list of dictionaries
that each contain a 'cidr' and optionally a matching 'gateway_ip'
instead of a list of CIDRs and a single gateway IP address. This
change to the init_l3 call signature is necessary because gateway
ports may now have multiple IP addresses.

Change-Id: I2f0093090ef3cd71c56801dee0b4c133d8bdb2f4
Depends-On: I150da5938e79eeef0c947ddb1a4282e37d0515ee
Partially-implements: blueprint multiple-ipv6-prefixes

This modifies the arguments to init_l3() to match the changes made
in the L3 Agent Linux driver as part of the multiple-ipv6-prefixes
blueprint.

The init_l3() method is changed to accept a list of dictionaries
that each contain a 'cidr' and optionally a matching 'gateway_ip'

ports may now have multiple IP addresses.

commit_message:
Introduce in-tree Rally specs

Most of OpenStack projects have specs.
Specs are documents in .rst format with fixed structure.
They allow developers to use standard gerrit code review approach
to discuss and align future changes in project.

This patch includes:

- doc/specs directory
- doc/specs readme files
- spec template.rst
- unit tests that checks that specs are regarding template

Change-Id: I31e0dbb8bcbc68ca40c67c643d44b27359906b9c

commit_message:
Adding manage/unmanage support for LeftHand driver

Added the needed methods needed to support manage/unmanage
in the HP LeftHand driver.

A minimum version check needed to be added as previous
versions of the LeftHand API won't support the manage/unmanage
feature.

Implements: blueprint lefthand-manage-unmanage
Change-Id: I1d118f579e19c04ee535de0f615de8a919fc3f80

commit_message:
Ironic: Move pxe_ipa-nv to check instead of experimental

The pxe_ipa-nv job is testing the future default ramdisk for Ironic, at
first we added it to experimetal just to make sure it works. Now that
we know it's passing we are moving it to the "check" so it can run on
every gate check for us to collect data and make it voting in the future.

Change-Id: I7187bdb1480cafa2f8152d0b0229a436c1fa3514

commit_message:
Make del_fdb_flow() idempotent

Addresses an issue where del_fdb_flow() gets a duplicate call for
the same port, which results in a KeyError. This change makes the
call more idempotent, so that it doesn't cause other follow-on
errors as a result of the uncaught exception.

Change-Id: I7a3a34dd654e143dee06c3e4642e859211a312ca
Closes-bug: #1421105
(cherry picked from commit 841b2f58f375df53b380cf5796bb31c82cd09260)

commit_message:
VMware: Support Multiple Datastores

Support for VMware store to use multiple datastore backends.

Spec (approved):
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/146723/

tl;dr:
1. Adds a new config option vmware_datastores to configure
   multiple datastores.
2. Implements a selection logic based on priority to choose
   from the list of datastores.
3. Modifies StoreLocation parsing logic to identify datastore
   related info from location URI.

DocImpact

Implements-Blueprint: vmware-store-multiple-datastores

Change-Id: I176f1143cd2d9b0a01a0f4f4256e7ac7d9b09afd

commit_message:
Add initial code for tempest tests

This is a bit of initial structure for some Tempest tests
intended to run in the devstack gates.

* Contains a single test case (list zones)
* Uses tempest_lib instead of tempest wherever possible
* Added a .testr.conf for use with testr
* Currently, needs keystone to get Designate's endpoint

commit_message:
Fix server schema for OS-EXT-IPS extension attributes

If "OS-EXT-IPS-MAC" & "OS-EXT-IPS" extension are enabled then,
server get & List detail response contains 'OS-EXT-IPS:type' and
'OS-EXT-IPS-MAC:mac_addr' attributes.

This patch adds those attribute in server response schema.

Change-Id: I371ee7621f26fd42e1c0ced51ba82b4477a3aa69

commit_message:
Use flavor stored with instance in vmware driver

Currently, the vmware driver calls Flavor.get_by_id() to retrieve
flavor extra_specs in order to spawn instances.

Since the flavor-from-sysmeta-to-blob patches merged, the instance
flavor is available from the instance itself. This change replaces
calls of Flavor.get_by_id() in the vmware driver with accesses of
the instance.flavor attribute.

Related to blueprint kilo-objects

Change-Id: I7ac19589d3e82ccea02ce0599cccd26301bf50f9

calls of Flavor.get_by_id() in the ironic driver with accesses of
the instance.flavor attribute.

commit_message:
Install openstackclient after other services

Let's see whether openstackclient will trigger unneeded version bump for
clients if its installation is put below all other services that are
expected to intall client libraries on proper versions on their own.

commit_message:
Remove the eventlet executor

We added the eventlet executor waiting for taskflow to land and be ready
for us to consume it. Now that we have it, it's time to remove the
eventlet executor in favor of taskflow's parallel executors.

DocImpact
UpgradeImpact

Partially-implements blueprint: new-upload-workflow

Change-Id: I220a14b2a92949772d5322c9947c42e892cfdbfa

commit_message:
Set rootfstype=ramfs for low memory Ironic nodes

When running with low memory (<1024), we need to switch from the default
rootfstype from tmpfs to ramfs to ensure nodes can decompress deployment
ramdisks.

Change-Id: I1b9dd614e592d99b2f59dea899b1ed3859ae0811

commit_message:
neutron-nec: Vendor code split

Neutron NEC plugin support is configured using DevStack external
plugin mechanism. The following needs to be added in local.conf:

Q_PLUGIN=nec
enable_plugin networking-nec https://git.openstack.org/stackforge/networking-nec

Also removes lib/neutron_thirdparty/trema and files/debs/trema.
DevStack external plugin for Trema Sliceable Switch is available
and the following is needed to enable it in DevStack.

enable_plugin trema-devstack-plugin https://github.com/nec-openstack/trema-devstack-plugin

Change-Id: If983b986355fcc0118b6e0446b3b295f23b3c40e

commit_message:
XenAPI: Default JEOS VM to only use 1GB RAM

While Devstack needs 4GB RAM (or more!) the JEOS
used as the base for the Devstack VM for XenServer
needs much less.  Allowing the initial install to
use 1GB means we have lower requirements overall

Change-Id: Iecaeeb4db0dffcc43c5532b5d57cb041d47047a6

commit_message:
Remove pip_lock_down from py_from_git role

This prevents pip rom being locked down on the hosts before the repo servers
are up. The hosts that don't have openstack services donn't require
pip to be locked down.

Change-Id: Ib21f603e460afea12ee0f8cfb4164cde588d8a28
Closes-Bug: #1429160

commit_message:
Set tcp_keepalive_time to 300 on MongoDB nodes

The default value of 30 seconds may cause socket errors between members
of a cluster. Setting it to 300 is recommended in the official
documentation[1].

Exclude controllers not to overwrite the fix for
Ic9d491f4904a5e665278027fc37254003c4b5172.

[1] http://docs.mongodb.org/manual/faq/diagnostics/

(Adapted from 1619deaf1133746f5205b3ae3136adadbb51b04e)

Closes-Bug: 1424919
Change-Id: If79702fbf51da8b68fde8a7f50f286656335cd5c

commit_message:
Set secure Ciphers and MACs for ssh server

Default configuration of sshd daemon on CentOS and Ubuntu server has
enabled ciphers and MACs which are considered as insecure. We can
explicit define list of ciphers without those which use CBC mode,
and not use old hmac algorithms.

Change-Id: Ie37efd9bafb10183e040df78ac1c896291376266
Closes-Bug: 1408595

commit_message:
Set secure Ciphers and MACs for ssh server

Default configuration of sshd daemon on CentOS and Ubuntu server has
enabled ciphers and MACs which are considered as insecure. We can
explicit define list of ciphers without those which use CBC mode,
and not use old hmac algorithms.

Change-Id: Ie37efd9bafb10183e040df78ac1c896291376266
Closes-Bug: 1408595

commit_message:
Rework the autohelp serialization of options

Using oslo.config objects in pickle leads to multiple import problems on
deserialization. Since we don't actually need oslo objects, we convert
them into dicts before dumping them.

Change-Id: Icbd1a3957e4d4ae05fe6227fbdd1cb58e5a3a98d

commit_message:
DRAC RAID testing -- DO NOT MERGE

The patch provides a way to manipulate target_raid_config from API. It
also adds client logging from Victor Lowther's DRAC BIOS config
patch.

This patch provides an easier way to test DRAC RAID configuration. It
doesn't supposed to be merged.

Change-Id: Ia3446eafb5cd4daab49a14333db7b31ee762fc27
